Name: Launchpad: Non-POS Merchant Boarding
Description:
The Launchpads Merchant Boarding API allows Worldpay partners to onboard merchants to Worldpay's Payments Platform. Please see the Getting Started page for more information.

To contact our certifications team, please email Certification2@fisglobal.com.
To contact the product team, please email APICustomerIntegration@fisglobal.com.

Fields.Name: externalRefId
Fields.Description: A unique GUID generated by POST resource, used for retrieving and updating a deal. Do not send in the request, API will always generate one and assign it to the deal.

Fields.Name: leadSource
Fields.Description: The source of a lead.

Fields.Name: guarantors
Fields.Description: Guarantor information. A guarantor is the person whose credit report will be pulled during the underwriting process.

Fields.Example: [{"type":"Mailing Address","addressLine1":"1234 W Tester Ave.","city":"City Town","state":"CO","country":"United States","postalCode":"80123","postalCodeExtension":"1234"},{"type":"Physical Address","addressLine1":"1234 W Tester Ave.","city":"City Town","state":"CO","country":"United States","postalCode":"80123","postalCodeExtension":"1234"}]
Fields.Name: addresses
salesAgent
Fields.Description: The agent who is submitting the deal.

Fields.Name: installationContact
Fields.Description: The Technical Agent who is going to do setup.

Fields.Name: routeToSalesRep
Fields.Description: Used to route a application to a worldpay or partner sales rep. By default the API is configured to route to a Worldpay sales rep. If you would like to route to partner (Launchpad UI) please work with your implementation consultant.

Fields.Name: dbaName
Fields.Description: The merchant name they do business as.  Generally with what their customers know the business.

Fields.Name: legalName
Fields.Description: Business Legal Name as filed with the IRS.

Fields.Name: ownershipType
Fields.Description: Required. OwnershipType defines the type of the Merchant Organization, and drives the requirements for data collections of beneficial and control owners under U.S. Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN).

Fields.Name: mccCode
Fields.Description: SIC Code / MCC Code (Merchant Category Code) is the code use to describe what the merchant is selling. Use MCC look up call to search valid codes, with sort and long description to find the MCC that most closely matches what the merchant is selling.

Fields.Name: businessEstablishedDate
Fields.Description: Date (CCYY-MM-DD) on which the merchant's business was established.

Fields.Name: websiteUrl
Fields.Description: The URL of the merchant's website.

Fields.Name: numberOfLocation
Fields.Description: Number of current locations.

Fields.Name: federalTaxId
Fields.Description: The Federal Tax ID is the business Tax Identification Number (TIN) or Employer Identification Number (EIN). If the business is a sole proprietor they may use the social security number of the sole proprietor.

Fields.Name: paymentAcceptanceMethod
Fields.Description: The ways in which the business is accepting payments. Multiple options may be selected. 'In person', would be card present at a brick and mortar store, 'onlinesite' would be card not present use on an ecommerce website, and 'phoneormailorder' would be card not present used for mail and telephone orders.

Fields.Name: pciadc
Fields.Description: Indication if the merchant has had an account data compromise.

Fields.Name: pcidssValidated
Fields.Description: Indictor showing if the merchant is compliant or not with the Payment Card Industry Data Security Standards.

Fields.Name: surroundingArea
Fields.Description: Type of area surroundning the business.

Fields.Name: productServiceSold
Fields.Description: Type of goods or services sold.

Fields.Name: ownAddYears
Fields.Description: Years the business has been operating in their current location.

Fields.Name: lengthOfContract
Fields.Description: Inital contract term in months.

Fields.Name: seasonal
Fields.Description: Does the business operate seasonally?

Fields.Name: activeMonths
Fields.Description: The months during which the business is actively operating.

Fields.Name: warranty
Fields.Description: Does the business offer warranties, dues, subscriptions, memberships, or other extended services?

Fields.Name: returnPolicy
Fields.Description: The business's return policy.

Fields.Name: acceptCreditCards
Fields.Description: Does the business accept credit cards?

Fields.Name: annualSalesVolume
Fields.Description: Projected annual sales volume.

Fields.Name: percentRetailSwipedTransactions
Fields.Description: Projected Percentage of daily card-present transactions.

Fields.Name: averageTicket
Fields.Description: Average ticket dollar amount.

Fields.Name: highestTicket
Fields.Description: Highest ticket dollar amount.

Fields.Name: currentProcessor
Fields.Description: the current processor

Fields.Name: acceptChargebacks
Fields.Description: Do you have more than 25 chargeback accepted in the last 12 months?

Fields.Name: chargebackPercent
Fields.Description:
Projected chargeback percentage.

```Required when acceptChargebacks is 'Yes'```

```Optional when acceptChargebacks is null or 'No'.```

Fields.Name: returnPercent
Fields.Description: Projected return percent of  goods sold

Fields.Name: cardNotPresentPercent
Fields.Description: Percent of card not present transactions.

Fields.Name: businessToBusinessPercent
Fields.Description: Percent of business-to-business transactions.

Fields.Name: internetTransactionPercent
Fields.Description: Percent of internet transactions.

Fields.Name: annualCreditSalesVolume
Fields.Description: Projected annual credit card sales volume.

Fields.Name: annualDebitSalesVolume
Fields.Description: Projected annual debit card sales volume.

Fields.Name: annualAmexVolume
Fields.Description: Projected annual Amex volume. ``` This field is required when you opt-in for Amex ```

Fields.Name: amexAverageTicket
Fields.Description:
AverageTicket dollar amount for Amex.
 ```This field is required when you opt-in for Amex```

Fields.Name: averageNumberofDays
Fields.Description: Average number of days from when cardholder is charged & when products or services are received IN FULL by cardholder.
